security.name: Super Micro Computer, Inc.
security.description: Super Micro Computer, Inc., commonly known as Supermicro, is a global leader in high-performance, high-efficiency server technology and innovation. Based in the United States, specifically San Jose, California, the company develops and provides end-to-end green computing solutions to data centers, cloud computing, enterprise IT, big data, high-performance computing, and Internet of Things environments. Founded in 1993, Supermicro emphasizes superior product design and uncompromising quality control to produce industry-leading serverboards, chassis, and server systems. The company's offerings include a broad range of high-performance systems and servers that are key in minimizing environmental impacts and operating costs for its clients. Supermicro's commitment to innovation is underscored by its advanced Server Building Block Solutions®, providing modular, interoperable components for diverse data center applications.

security.name: Applied DNA Sciences, Inc.
security.description: Applied DNA Sciences, Inc., based in the United States, operates within the biotechnology sector, primarily focusing on the development of DNA-based technology solutions. The company's endeavors encompass a broad range of applications, including anti-counterfeiting and product authentication technologies, which utilize unique DNA markers to verify the authenticity of various commercial and consumer products. A significant project for Applied DNA Sciences includes its work in the textiles industry, providing traceable DNA markers to ensure the integrity and origin of fabrics throughout global supply chains. Additionally, the company is actively involved in the development of molecular diagnostics, offering platforms that enable the detection and diagnostics of pathogens for healthcare and biosecurity purposes.
